To specify a datatype, either type in your entry or select a datatype from 
the list of choices. The following rules apply:

  * Use a datatype consistent with the function of the local variable (for 
    example, if the value of the hidden field is a name, use a character 
    datatype).

  * If you are using a record type array, do not include the string 
    "ARRAY OF" in your record type name. Use the "Array?" field to 
    indicate that the record type is an array.

  * If you select a datatype from the list, you must edit the entry to 
    replace any lower case text with a value. For example, if you 
    select "I(length)," you must change "length" to a numeric value. 
    Similarly, if you select a "TYPE OF" datatype, enter the actual names 
    of the form, table, or table field you are using.
